arStrings.szText: Dian has returned to life once again. It is time to free him from the cycle.

Once again, Dian has returned to life without any memory. However, I now know that it is the ring he was given by the demon that is causing this strange resurrection. 

We must speak with Elder Suharti, who may know more.

The Elder explained that the "old man" is actually a trickster demon named Beleth.

Dian's father once hunted the creature with a blessed sword, but was unable to destroy him. Dian now has the unenviable task of exhuming his father's grave and retrieving the sword.

Dian has retrieved his father's sword, and now we must collect a rod of living hazel wood. Elder Suharti believes that if the demon attempts to flee, we can force it to materialize by using the rod to make the sign of the triangle in its presence.
We are both armed. Me with the rod of living hazel wood and Dian with his father's blessed sword. We go now to destroy the demon Beleth and free Dian and his family from this curse forever.

Dian bravely stood against the demon Beleth, and together we destroyed the creature. However, as the curse broke, Dian was forced to relive the hundreds of deaths he experienced at the hands of the demon. I should check on him in Samuk to ensure he is all right.
